description:
Recently sold: $312,000. Contact the official listing agent, Julie Betzler with Realty Group Inc for the most accurate and up to date information on this awesome property!  Fantastic 3-level split-entry home with fully finished walkout lower level. Property is on huge .62 acres, fenced backyard with gates, firepit, hot tub (stays with home), back 12? x 13? deck and awesome 21? x 30? second garage, great for additional storage! Home is finished with approximately 3,123 square feet includes hard-to-find 7 bedrooms (3 on the upper main level and 4 on the lower level).  Property backs up to parks, trails, Shingle Creek, and is close to  restaurants, major roadways/694, conveniences and middle and high schools!  Call it home today!!

This home was built in 1967, has had several updates including kitchen, both baths, porch addition, some carpet, paint and more!  It has great curb appeal with landscaping, level yard, gutters and front storm door, concrete driveway, 2 car attached tuckunder garage, plus 2nd detached garage/storage shed.  

The upper main level features a welcoming living room with front yard facing windows, neutral carpet, wood rails, and opens to the informal dining room with glass doors that leads out to the 4-season porch addition.  The kitchen has been updated with stainless appliances, modern backsplash, has lots of task lighting, counter prep space, breakfast bar seating and loads of cabinets.  The floors are tile, Oak cabinets and check out the beautiful glass front cabinet doors for display.

The upper main level also features three bedrooms on one level, which is hard to find in a split entry style home (large upper level footprint). The full upper level bathroom has been fully updated, includes tile surround, tile floors, double vanity.  There is a also a gorgeous 4-season back porch addition with vaulted ceilings, ceiling fan and beautiful backyard views, plus access to the back deck.  There is an upper bonus area above the garage that features a spacious family room with wood burning fireplace, front and back views, great for entertaining and relaxing! (big screen and projection equipment does not stay)

description: Recently sold: $625,000. Large walkout 2 story with craftsman-inspired details. Many wonderful updates including in-ground pool, 450 sqft guesthouse with loft, 3/4 bath, skylight, wet bar, & exterior wood-burning fireplace. Beautiful attached screened porch & deck overlooking pool and patio. Landscaped yard with wrought iron fencing. Property is adjacent to Three Rivers Regional Park trail. Many custom built-in cabinets, shelving, and desks throughout home. Huge 4 car garage with great storage & shelving. Spacious modern kitchen with large granite island & counters, maple flooring, cherry cabinets, stainless appliances, & large windows overlooking yard. Owners suite with 2 walk-in closets, full bath, vaulted ceiling, and private office. Master bath features separate jetted tub & tiled shower, 2 sinks, and in-floor heating. Walk-out basement with exercise room, movie room with seating, 3/4 bath, 5th bedroom, and family room with pool table. New furnace, A/C, carpet, paint, & roof.
Recently sold: $305,000. Traditional 2 story walkout. 5 bedrooms and laundry all on the same level. Unfinished basement for expansion. SOLD BEFORE PRINT.

description: Recently sold: $427,000. Executive two story on the 15th Fairway of Edinburgh Golf Course. Home features nice updates plus, 4 large bedrooms, separate main floor office (could be playroom, 5th bedroom, etc). Enjoy 2 fireplaces with one on main floor and another in lower level. Many updates including new Carrier Furnace/AC 2016 (zoned heating & cooling), new roof 2016, also most windows replaced with Andersen Windows, updated lighting and more. Home also has home generator and many smart home features as well. Great location, close to parks, trails, and many amenities.

Close to local amenities and is available for immediate possession.

description: Recently sold: $360,000. Overlooking a tranquil and serene lake, you will find this stunning Lundgren built walkout 2-Story home with an amazing and open floor plan and loaded with custom details throughout.  This 3 bedroom, 3 bath home features gleaming hardwood floors, ceramic tile, custom cabinets, and plenty of room-to-grow.  The main floor of this home offers a formal Living Room, Dining that is open to the designer Kitchen with center island breakfast bar, spacious Family Room with a cozy fireplace and door to the screened porch, exquisite Master Suite with a beautiful Whirlpool bath, Laundry/Mud Room, and a 1/2 bath.  On the upper level, there is a loft, 2 spacious bedrooms, and a full bath.  The walkout lower level is ready-to-finish with your personal touch and imagination?add a Rec Room, Theater, 4th Bedroom, 4th Bath, Hobby Room, etc.  This well cared for and maintained home has many updates including new water heater, new air conditioner, new furnace blower, new gutters, Pottery Barn blinds in the Family Room, Pottery Barn chandelier in the Dining, and much more.  In addition, this home features extensive landscaping surrounding the home and backs to walking/bike trails and the peaceful lake where you will enjoy wildlife and beautiful sunsets.  Great neighborhood in Lakeside at Oxbow Commons where you will also enjoy the swimming pool.

description: Recently sold: $301,000.

Recently sold: $295,000. In the charming community of Wickford Village is the Newport D, a spacious townhouse with four bedrooms, three-and-a-half bathrooms and a two-car garage.
The well designed kitchen offers dark granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, stunning cafe stained upgraded cabinetry, an enlarged center island, laminate flooring and cabinet hardware.  The owner's suite is a retreat with oversized walk-in closet and features a private garden bath with large soaking bathtub and heightened double bowl vanity.  This home has many upgraded amenities including custom paint, washer and dryer, antique bronze lighting package and upgraded carpeting and pad. The lower level has a bonus finished bedroom and full bathroom, a great designated area for guests.
This 2,250 square foot new townhouse is located at 9639 Scott Avenue North in Brooklyn Park just north of highway 610. Wickford Village is ideally situated near local retailers, minutes from Arbor Lakes, and offers great highway access to downtown Minneapolis. Enjoy walking trails, surrounding city parks, neighboring golf courses and more.
This home is available for move in immediately.
For more information about the Newport D, contact Paul Hallman at the Wickford Village Sales Center 763-392-7586.

You will love the large living room and spacious kitchen with center island, new flooring, raised panel cabinets, newer appliances, and more. Three spacious bedrooms upstairs with walk-in closet. Four bedrooms (3 on the upper level all with walk-in closets) including the master bedroom which offers  3/4 master bathroom. Entertain family and friends in the lower level family room with gas fireplace and plenty of space for a game table, desk, toys, exercise equipment, etc... There is an additional bedroom and guest 3/4 bath on this level. The fourth level offers the option of using as is for your storage needs or finishing a fifth bedroom (egress window already in) and even room for a study, playroom, etc... Gotta love the oversized lot and three car garage!
